## 4. Features Not Yet Built (from Strategic Plan)

These are planned features that are not in the current MVP:

### High Priority (V1.0 / Weeks 13–20)
- [ ] **Additional workflow modes** — only Centralized (Mode 1) is built; Ministry-First, Hybrid, and Self-Service are defined in constants but not implemented
- [ ] **SMS reminders via Twilio** — the reminder channel options exist in the UI but SMS sending is not wired up (only email via Resend works)
- [ ] **Volunteer self-service portal** — volunteers currently confirm via token links but can't log in to set availability, blockout dates, or frequency preferences themselves
- [ ] **Household linking** — data model supports it but no UI for linking family members or preventing household conflicts in the scheduler
- [ ] **ChMS integrations** — Planning Center, Breeze, Rock RMS API imports (currently CSV/manual only)
- [ ] **Annual billing option** — Stripe supports this but checkout currently only offers monthly; strategic plan mentions 20% annual discount
- [ ] **Overage pricing** — plan mentions $5/50 extra volunteers, $10/5 extra ministries above tier limits (not implemented)

### Medium Priority (V1.0+)
- [ ] **Substitution engine** — listed as Growth tier feature; allow volunteers to request subs and auto-match
- [ ] **Advanced rotations** — 2-on/4-off patterns, seasonal roles, skill-based assignment
- [ ] **PWA / mobile optimization** — service workers for offline, installable app
- [ ] **Audit log** — who changed what, when
- [ ] **Zapier integration** — trigger on schedule changes

### Lower Priority (V1.5+ / Months 6–12)
- [ ] **Multi-site support** — per-campus services, cross-site leadership
- [ ] **What-if scheduler** — sandbox mode to test changes before publishing
- [ ] **White-label** — custom branding for Pro/Enterprise tiers
- [ ] **API access** — listed as Pro tier feature, public API for third-party integrations
- [ ] **Horizontal expansion** — schools, nonprofits (messaging pivot)

