## Quick Reference: Environment Variables to Update for Production

When switching from test to live mode, update these in **both** `.env.local` and **Vercel Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables**:

| Variable | Current (Test) | Action Needed |
|----------|---------------|---------------|
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | `sk_test_...` | Replace with `sk_live_...` |
| `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` | `whsec_...` | New secret from live webhook |
| `STRIPE_PRICE_STARTER` | `price_...` (test) | New ID from live product |
| `STRIPE_PRICE_GROWTH` | `price_...` (test) | New ID from live product |
| `STRIPE_PRICE_PRO` | `price_...` (test) | New ID from live product |
| `RESEND_API_KEY` | Current key | Verify domain first |

Firebase keys (`NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_*`) stay the same — they're the same project in prod.
